{
  "stem": "13063.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So in this itself, this has a certain percentage of animalization of a person.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Of course, we did not give up the faith in Hashem, the faith in God.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Those who, who had the background.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "On the contrary, somebody-- I think Schindler, it was Schindler who smuggled [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] the head [NON-ENGLISH], the head phylactery into the camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And every morning, there was a, there was a line of people, standing to put on one [NON-ENGLISH] and say, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] Next, next, next.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "In this starvation, there was Pesach, in April '45.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There were holy people in the camp who did not want to eat this piece of little-- little piece of bread that we got every morning.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because they wanted-- I mean, they were-- they, they, they had a, a sense of commitment, such deep commitment, to the Jewish way of life, to the Jewish religion and to Hashem, To God's-- to Torah, that they had foregone the little piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they ate roots, grass.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "All through the Pesach.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I ate bread.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because the Rabbis told me, you need to eat as, as much as you can and whatever you can .",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Because this is [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] This is something that might save your soul.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It might save your body.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very hard to eat bread on Pesach.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never ate bread, never ate before bread on Pesach.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I did eat.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As a commitment to Torah, as a show of commitment to Torah, I preferred not to-- on the Seder night not to eat anything.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I fasted on Seder night, just to, to show that when I do eat bread the next morning, it will be because I have to.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
